The paper proposes a method for domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on heterogeneous domain adaptation, where the source and target domains are different. The proposed method involves learning a domain-shared classifier and a domain-invariant subspace in an end-to-end manner. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. 

The experiments involve transfer tasks of image-to-image, text-to-image, and text-to-text, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. 

Finally, the paper involves working with images and text, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category. 

Therefore, the 5 likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.MM, ordered from most to least likely.
